
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ali-pce-remote-initiated-lsp-usage-00.pdf'>
    <title>"Path Computation Element Communication Protocol (PCEP) Extensions for remote-initiated LSP Usage", Zafar Ali, Siva Sivabalan, Clarence Filsfils, Robert Varga, Victor Lopez, Oscar de Dios, Xian Zhang</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ali-pce-remote-initiated-lsp-usage-00.pdf</link>
    <description>When active stateful PCE is used for managing PCE-initiated LSP, PCC may not be aware of the intended usage of the LSP (e.g., in a multi-layer network). PCEP Extensions for PCE-initiated MPLS and GMPLS LSP Setup specifications do not address this requirement. This draft addresses the requirement to specify on how PCC should use the remote initiated LSPs.</description>
    <dc:date>2013-10-20T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
